  <selectFromSequence from="2" to="5" step="1" name="a" />
  <selectFromSequence from="2" to="9" step="1" name="b" exclude="$a/2 3*$a/2 $a 2*$a 3*$a 4*$a" />

  <math name="a2" simplify>$a^2</math>
  <math name="xo" simplify>0</math>
  <select assignNames="(yo)">
    <option><math>-$a</math></option>
    <option><math>$a</math></option>
  </select>
  <math name="P">($xo,$yo)</math>
  <function symbolic name="G" formula="y^2*(y^2 - $a2)" />
  <function symbolic name="F" formula="x^2*(x^2 - $b)" />
  <math name="tan_line">y=$yo</math>
</setup>

<p>
  Use implicit differentiation to find
  an equation of the tangent line to the
  <alert>devil's curve</alert>, defined by
  <m> $G = $F </m>, at the point <m>$P</m>.
</p>
<p>
  An equation of the
  tangent line to the devil's curve at
  the given point is
  <answer><award>$tan_line</award></answer>
</p>

<solution>
  <setup>
    <math name="ta2" simplify>2*$a^2</math>
    <math name="tb" simplify>2*$b</math>
    <math name="tyo3" simplify>2*$yo^3</math>
  </setup>
  Writing the equation as
  <m>y^4 - $a2 y^2 = x^4 - $b x^2</m>,
  and then differentiating implicitly
  with respect to <m>x</m>, gives
  <me>
    (4 y^3 - $ta2 y) \, \frac{dy}{dx}
      = 4 x^3 - $tb x.
  </me>
  If <m>x = $xo</m> and <m>y = $yo</m>,
  then this last equation becomes
  <me>
    $tyo3 \, \frac{dy}{dx} = 0,
    \qquad \text{and so} \qquad
    \frac{dy}{dx} = 0,
  </me>
  which means that the tangent line
  is horizontal.  Therefore, the
  tangent line to the devil's curve
  at the point <m>$P</m> is defined
  by the equation <m>$tan_line</m>.
</solution>
